column5: BCG is most commonly affects the underpriviliged persons#Comma living in the areas with poor sanitation and those that are malnourished or immunocompromised. It is a vaccine primarily used against tuberculosis(TB).
Polio is caused by Polio virus#Comma an RNA virus of the Picornaviridae family. OPV (Oral Polio Vaccine) is a vaccine#Comma used to prevent poliomyelitis (polio)
Hepatitis B is caused by HBV#Comma a DNA virus of the Hepadnaviridae family.#NewlineIt is a serious condition which can become chronic and lead to liver cirrhosis.#Newline

DPT (also DTP and DTwP) refers to a class of combination vaccines against three infectious diseases in humans: diphtheria#Comma pertussis and tetanus. The vaccine components include diptheria and tetanus toxoids and killed whole cells of the bacterium that causes pertussis.
Haempphilus influenza type b is a major cause of meningitis#Comma pneumonia#Comma and epiglottittis in infants and young children.
Rotavirus is an important cause of severe gastroenteritis in infants and young children#Comma around the world.

MMR vaccine protects against three diseases: measles#Comma mumps#Comma and rubella. CDC recommends children get two doses of MMR vaccine#Comma starting with the first dose at 12 through 15 months of age#Comma and the second dose at 4 through 6 years of age.
Chickenpox is a very contagious disease caused by the varicella-zoster virus. The best way to prevent chickenpox is to get the Varicella vaccine.
Hepatitis A is a vaccine-preventable#Comma communicable disease of the liver caused by the hepatitis A virus. The best way to prevent hepatitis A infection is to get vaccinated.
PCV helps to prevent pneumococcal disease#Comma which is any type of infection caused by Streptococcus pneumoniae bacteria.
